EXEROISE II

MILTIADES

I. It happens that Miltiades wishes to be sent with the colonists to Chersonesus. The Athenians send messengers to enquire whom they had best employ as leader, since a war must be waged with the Thracians. They are-directed by Pythia to take Miltiades as their, general. “If you do thiS,'' she says (inquit), “your undertaking will be prosperous.''

The Lemnians will voluntarily come under the power of the Athenians when Miltiades can sail from Athens to Lemnos with the north wind.
